23/04/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The opposition Democratic Party (DP) said on Tuesday (22 April) it would call for a parliamentary debate on measures against organised crime.
DP described the alarming level of organised crime as "a disturbance to the entire Albanian society".
The DP caucus also called for more active involvement by President Alfred Moisiu in the fight against trafficking and crime.
(Shekulli - 23/04/03;
ATA - 22/04/03)
